RunConfig – How and Why I Used It
What is RunConfig?

RunConfig is a configuration object provided by the agents framework that defines how the Runner executes an Agent. It contains settings like:

Model: Specifies which AI model the Agent should use.

Model provider: Specifies the client for API calls (AsyncOpenAI in this case).

Tracing or logging settings: Enable or disable tracing for cleaner outputs.

How I Used It

Created a separate file run_config.py for modularity:

from agents import AsyncOpenAI, OpenAIChatCompletionsModel
from agents.run import RunConfig

client = AsyncOpenAI(api_key=GEMINI_API_KEY)
model = OpenAIChatCompletionsModel(model="gemini-2.0-flash-001", openai_client=client)
run_config = RunConfig(model=model, model_provider=client, tracing_disabled=True)

Imported run_config in my FastAPI app:

from run_config import run_config

Used it in Runner to execute the Agent:

result = await Runner.run(
    starting_agent=agent,
    input=query.question,
    context=context,
    run_config=run_config
)
Why I Used RunConfig

Provides centralized control over model execution.

Makes it easy to reuse across multiple files or agents.

Ensures the Agent logic is decoupled from configuration details.

Enables tracing/logging control without modifying Agent code.

Supports scalable and maintainable architecture.

Tools Implemented

list_products – List all products.

calculate_total – Compute total cost for a product and quantity.

recommend_product – Suggest the cheapest product.

These tools are registered with the Agent and called automatically as needed.

What I Learned

Modular Design: Extracting RunConfig into its own file allows reusability and cleaner code.

Separation of Concerns: Agent logic is independent of execution configuration.

Runner Execution Flow: Learned how Runner.run() uses RunConfig to execute tools and generate AI responses.

Tool-Based Interaction: Realized how to design AI assistants that use multiple tools and structured context.

Logging & Debugging: Instrumenting logging in FastAPI, tools, and Agent execution helps track flow and errors.